position : absolute (parent element which has its position as relative)


Resetting and body
*{
    margin : 0;
    padding :0;
    box-sizing:border-box;
}

body{
    font-family: "Lato", sans-serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color : #777;
    padding: 30px;
}



length in % (height , padding , margin) always related to parent width


font based units -- em , rem

em font -- x * parent font size

em length (padding ,margin) --- x * uses font size of current element


rem always uses root both font and lenfth



View port based :
vh  1% of view port height

vw  1% of view port width


display 

block 100%of parent width and create line break

inline :
No height and width
only left and right padding and margin

inlie-block->
no line break , only content space applies box model



Positions :
relative : normal flow 
absolute : taken out of normal flow , No impact on surrounding contents , it can overlap elements on same sapce



